---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CategoryHero from '../../../components/CategoryHero.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../../../components/TableOfContents.astro';

const title = "A Week in the Swiss Alps";
const description = "Journey through picturesque mountain villages and hidden valleys in Switzerland.";
const publishDate = "2024-03-15";

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Blog", href: "/blog" },
  { name: "Travel Stories", href: "/blog/travel-stories" },
  { name: title, href: "" }
];

const tableOfContents = [
  { text: "Planning the Journey", slug: "planning-the-journey" },
  { text: "Zermatt and the Matterhorn", slug: "zermatt-and-the-matterhorn" },
  { text: "Lauterbrunnen Valley", slug: "lauterbrunnen-valley" },
  { text: "Grindelwald Adventures", slug: "grindelwald-adventures" },
  { text: "Photography Tips", slug: "photography-tips" },
  { text: "Practical Information", slug: "practical-information" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Breadcrumbs paths={breadcrumbs} />
  
  <CategoryHero
    title={title}
    description={description}
    image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531986362435-16b427eb9c26"
  />

  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-4 lg:gap-8">
      <!-- Table of Contents - Desktop -->
      <div class="hidden lg:block">
        <div class="sticky top-4">
          <TableOfContents headings={tableOfContents} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-3">
        <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">
            Published on {new Date(publishDate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
              year: 'numeric',
              month: 'long',
              day: 'numeric'
            })}
          </div>

          <p class="lead text-xl">
            The Swiss Alps offer some of the most breathtaking mountain landscapes in the world. Join me on a week-long journey through picturesque villages, hidden valleys, and majestic peaks.
          </p>

          <h2 id="planning-the-journey">Planning the Journey</h2>
          <p>
            Our adventure began in Zurich, where we caught the efficient Swiss train to our first destination: Zermatt. The journey itself was a preview of the spectacular scenery to come, with the train winding through valleys and alongside crystal-clear lakes.
          </p>

          <h2 id="zermatt-and-the-matterhorn">Zermatt and the Matterhorn</h2>
          <p>
            Zermatt, a car-free village nestled at the foot of the iconic Matterhorn, served as our base for the first three days. The early morning light on the Matterhorn created perfect conditions for photography, while the charming village streets offered endless opportunities for street photography.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            <p>"The Matterhorn at sunrise is a sight that every photographer should experience at least once."</p>
          </blockquote>

          <h2 id="lauterbrunnen-valley">Lauterbrunnen Valley</h2>
          <p>
            Our next stop was the Lauterbrunnen Valley, often called the Valley of 72 Waterfalls. The sheer cliffs and cascading waterfalls create a landscape that seems straight out of a fairy tale. The highlight was photographing Staubbach Falls as the morning light created rainbows in the mist.
          </p>

          <h2 id="grindelwald-adventures">Grindelwald Adventures</h2>
          <p>
            In Grindelwald, we found ourselves surrounded by the dramatic north face of the Eiger. The First Cliff Walk provided heart-stopping views and unique photography opportunities. Early morning hikes to Lake Bachalpsee offered perfect reflections of the surrounding peaks.
          </p>

          <h2 id="photography-tips">Photography Tips</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Bring a sturdy tripod for sunrise/sunset shots</li>
            <li>Use polarizing filters for glacier and lake photography</li>
            <li>Pack weather-sealed gear - mountain weather changes quickly</li>
            <li>Consider a drone for unique perspectives (check local regulations)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="practical-information">Practical Information</h2>
          <h3>Best Time to Visit</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Summer (June-August) for hiking and wildflowers</li>
            <li>Fall (September-October) for fewer crowds</li>
            <li>Winter (December-March) for snow photography</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Transportation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Swiss Travel Pass for unlimited train travel</li>
            <li>Mountain railways and cable cars included</li>
            <li>Efficient connections between villages</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Photography Equipment</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Wide-angle lens (16-35mm)</li>
            <li>Telephoto lens (70-200mm)</li>
            <li>Neutral density filters</li>
            <li>Polarizing filter</li>
            <li>Sturdy tripod</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Planning Your Own Trip?</h3>
            <p>
              Check out our detailed <a href="/travel-guides/nature/swiss-alps">Swiss Alps Photography Guide</a> for more technical tips and location information.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>